  "prompt": "Why is M&M's motto \"melts in your mouth, not in your hand\"?",
  "response": "The famous M&M's slogan was created as a practical solution to a common problem with chocolate. During World War II, soldiers were issued chocolate bars that would often melt in hot climates, making them messy and difficult to eat. Forrest Mars Sr. observed soldiers eating chocolate pellets coated in a hard sugar shell, which prevented melting, and was inspired to create M&M's. \n\nThe milk chocolate candies were designed with a hard candy shell that would prevent the chocolate from melting when held, allowing people to eat them easily without getting their hands messy. The slogan directly highlights this unique feature of the candy, pointing out that the chocolate remains intact in your hand but melts smoothly in your mouth when eaten.\n\nThe slogan was first introduced in 1954 and became one of the most recognizable advertising slogans in confectionery history, effectively communicating the candy's key selling point.",
